WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:02.510 --> 00:00:04.260
Misfortune is like a snake.

2
00:00:04.670 --> 00:00:06.640
They slither over silently.

3
00:00:06.990 --> 00:00:10.990
and viciously bite the ankles
of those standing defenseless and still.

4
00:00:13.540 --> 00:00:15.800
I heard your dad killed someone.

5
00:00:16.540 --> 00:00:19.390
Wow. So do you know how to kill people?

6
00:00:22.860 --> 00:00:24.080
You are a murderer.

7
00:00:24.260 --> 00:00:25.630
You are a murderer.

8
00:00:26.240 --> 00:00:28.200
Chaeha. the son of a murderer.

9
00:00:28.580 --> 00:00:30.320
The casino boss murder case.

10
00:00:30.550 --> 00:00:32.729
Don't come near me.
It might be transmittable.

11
00:00:32.729 --> 00:00:36.930
-You are a murderer.
-Oh. he's the son of the murderer. Lee Gilyoung. right?

12
00:00:37.310 --> 00:00:39.810
Be careful. They say murder is hereditary.

13
00:00:40.170 --> 00:00:42.660
No wonder. I knew
there was something about his eyes.

14
00:00:42.660 --> 00:00:45.650
You are a murderer. You are a murderer.

15
00:00:45.890 --> 00:00:48.830
You are a murderer. You are a murderer.

16
00:00:49.630 --> 00:00:52.760
I tried my best to hold my head high
and grit my teeth

17
00:00:54.120 --> 00:00:57.130
[Lee Chaeha]

18
00:00:54.180 --> 00:00:56.780
just so I wouldn't be swallowed
by misfortune.

19
00:00:57.410 --> 00:00:59.840
[Lee Chaeha.
Supreme Prosecutors' Office]

20
00:01:00.030 --> 00:01:01.550
Lee Chaeha...

21
00:01:06.560 --> 00:01:07.370
you are...

22
00:01:07.620 --> 00:01:08.310
a...

23
00:01:08.440 --> 00:01:09.410
murderer's

24
00:01:09.860 --> 00:01:12.610
son. right?

25
00:01:15.910 --> 00:01:18.650
The killer of Kang Woosung.

26
00:01:19.030 --> 00:01:20.080
Lee...

27
00:01:20.700 --> 00:01:21.789
Gil...

28
00:01:22.560 --> 00:01:23.539
young's

29
00:01:24.370 --> 00:01:25.539
son.

30
00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:33.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

31
00:01:36.240 --> 00:01:38.210
I'm not like him.

32
00:01:38.860 --> 00:01:40.920
Don't lump us together just because.

33
00:01:41.590 --> 00:01:44.650
Then I can assume
you're willing to work with me. right?

34
00:01:45.420 --> 00:01:46.340
Ah.

35
00:01:47.280 --> 00:01:49.450
If you don't like this sequence.

36
00:01:49.870 --> 00:01:51.670
I'll make a formal proposal.

37
00:01:51.920 --> 00:01:53.120
Director Lee Chaeha.

38
00:01:57.750 --> 00:01:59.110
would you work with me?

39
00:02:05.890 --> 00:02:07.960
[Park Siwoo]

40
00:02:10.490 --> 00:02:12.690
[Kim Yunsik]

41
00:02:18.050 --> 00:02:19.880
[Kwak Seunghwan]
[Because of inheritance?]

42
00:02:20.550 --> 00:02:22.190
[Koryoin Mr. Kim overdosed on drugs]

43
00:02:22.470 --> 00:02:23.980
[Found in a small room
on the second floor]

44
00:02:24.120 --> 00:02:26.300
[The Last Abandoned Mine in Danhyeon City
To Be Turned Into a Casino]

45
00:02:27.040 --> 00:02:29.060
[Led by Ohsong Construction. 'Danhyeon Land' Integrated Resort (Casino. Hotel. Theme Park) to be built—
Officially secures $400M in foreign investment]

46
00:02:29.170 --> 00:02:33.680
[Casino Industry's First Female Executive…
Pledges "Transparent Operations. Regional Co-Prosperity"]

47
00:02:33.690 --> 00:02:35.340
[Danhyeon City "Casino Boss Murdered"...
Suspect Identified as Driver. Mr. Lee]

48
00:02:41.890 --> 00:02:44.280
[The Prosecutor's Proposal]

49
00:02:51.750 --> 00:02:53.540
[Prosecutor Joo Taeseon] [Investigator Song Haneul]
[Investigator Lee Chaeha] [Room 512]

50
00:03:11.150 --> 00:03:13.010
Nice to meet you. I'm Song Haneul.

51
00:03:13.640 --> 00:03:15.610
Hello. I'm Lee Chaeha.

52
00:03:16.600 --> 00:03:18.320
Oh. let me help you.

53
00:03:22.460 --> 00:03:23.520
By the way. Mr. Lee.

54
00:03:24.920 --> 00:03:27.400
it hasn't been long since you came
to Danhyeon District Office. have you?

55
00:03:27.400 --> 00:03:29.260
I know almost everyone here.

56
00:03:29.370 --> 00:03:31.030
but you look a bit unfamiliar.

57
00:03:32.470 --> 00:03:35.130
You don't have to be too afraid
of Prosecutor Ju.

58
00:03:35.280 --> 00:03:38.340
As rumored. he's very efficient.

59
00:03:38.579 --> 00:03:42.120
But unlike the rumors.
he's very tolerant of his staff.

60
00:03:42.390 --> 00:03:44.390
Well. even if your preparation
is a bit lacking.

61
00:03:44.390 --> 00:03:45.860
he won't say much.

62
00:03:47.370 --> 00:03:51.190
However. I think boundaries
are very important.

63
00:03:51.370 --> 00:03:53.010
Don't ask personal questions

64
00:03:53.010 --> 00:03:54.410
and don't be too curious.

65
00:03:55.050 --> 00:03:56.880
Also. when reviewing cases.

66
00:03:57.070 --> 00:03:58.630
organize the case files well.

67
00:03:58.630 --> 00:04:01.380
Just find details of relevant laws
and similar precedents that

68
00:04:01.380 --> 00:04:02.570
can be applied in court for him.

69
00:04:02.570 --> 00:04:03.760
Laws and precedents...

70
00:04:03.760 --> 00:04:04.590
Yeah.

71
00:04:04.860 --> 00:04:07.520
Also. he doesn't like typos

72
00:04:07.650 --> 00:04:09.170
and hates omitted subjects.

73
00:04:09.170 --> 00:04:11.280
He wants transcripts to be
as detailed and clear as possible.

74
00:04:11.280 --> 00:04:13.620
No misunderstandings and no confusion
will be tolerated.

75
00:04:13.620 --> 00:04:14.830
Thank you.

76
00:04:16.730 --> 00:04:17.670
Mr. Lee.

77
00:04:18.579 --> 00:04:20.180
Do you live in the provided apartment?

78
00:04:20.180 --> 00:04:21.079
Yes.

79
00:04:21.750 --> 00:04:23.030
I live on the 5th floor.

80
00:04:23.410 --> 00:04:26.400
We live in the same building;
how come we've never met?

81
00:04:26.400 --> 00:04:28.530
Maybe we just kept missing each other.

82
00:04:33.880 --> 00:04:35.800
If you want to thank me.
let's have a meal next time.

83
00:04:35.800 --> 00:04:36.570
Sure.

84
00:04:37.180 --> 00:04:38.510
Give it to me. I'll do it.

85
00:04:38.590 --> 00:04:39.690
No. I'll do it.

86
00:04:39.810 --> 00:04:40.870
Oh. I'll do it. Give it to me.

87
00:04:40.870 --> 00:04:41.930
It's fine. really.

88
00:04:41.990 --> 00:04:43.790
Come on. I'll do it. Give it to me.

89
00:04:45.200 --> 00:04:46.260
You're here.

90
00:04:51.840 --> 00:04:54.040
Supervisor Lee Chaeha. please come in.

91
00:04:54.409 --> 00:04:55.420
Ah. got it.

92
00:05:08.170 --> 00:05:10.970
This is the autopsy report
of the Koryoin. Mr. Kim.

93
00:05:12.560 --> 00:05:13.740
What's the conclusion?

94
00:05:13.740 --> 00:05:15.580
The autopsy revealed meth
at 1.000 times the lethal dose

95
00:05:15.580 --> 00:05:17.520
and a small amount of nicotine.

96
00:05:17.950 --> 00:05:19.220
There is no suspicion of homicide.

97
00:05:19.220 --> 00:05:21.530
It seems he died
during the meth injection.

98
00:05:21.530 --> 00:05:24.160
A junkie died from overdose.

99
00:05:24.330 --> 00:05:25.390
Is there anything suspicious?

100
00:05:25.390 --> 00:05:26.810
A needle mark was found on his neck.

101
00:05:26.810 --> 00:05:30.960
There were also plastic fragments found
not just in his mouth but also in his stomach.

102
00:05:30.960 --> 00:05:32.890
There were also scratches
on his esophagus.

103
00:05:32.890 --> 00:05:35.150
The causes of these can't be determined.

104
00:05:36.540 --> 00:05:37.550
[Opinion of non-prosecution (non-referral)
regarding suspect Alexander Kim]

105
00:05:37.260 --> 00:05:38.970
The police recommended
non-prosecution of the case.

106
00:05:38.970 --> 00:05:42.070
There were no witnesses at the scene.
and no CCTV footage.

107
00:05:42.070 --> 00:05:45.270
We also couldn't trace his whereabouts
after he entered the country.

108
00:05:45.270 --> 00:05:46.600
That's what's strange.

109
00:05:46.620 --> 00:05:48.620
How could this Koryoin.
who has been in the country for just a day.

110
00:05:48.620 --> 00:05:51.920
know the route
and avoid all the CCTVs in Danhyeon?

111
00:05:52.570 --> 00:05:55.700
Especially since this was near
a casino with many CCTVs.

112
00:05:56.060 --> 00:06:00.310
Unless someone in Danhyeon
told him the route beforehand.

113
00:06:00.520 --> 00:06:01.980
As I mentioned.

114
00:06:02.130 --> 00:06:04.940
it seems Koryoin Mr. Kim was selling meth.

115
00:06:05.270 --> 00:06:06.260
Where's the evidence?

116
00:06:06.260 --> 00:06:07.620
It's body packing.

117
00:06:08.150 --> 00:06:10.740
You can look at the last attachment.

118
00:06:10.890 --> 00:06:14.830
It's a drug smuggling method
commonly used overseas since the 80s.

119
00:06:15.010 --> 00:06:17.510
There have been similar drug trafficking cases
in the country before too.

120
00:06:17.510 --> 00:06:20.210
If Mr. Kim is a drug dealer.

121
00:06:20.650 --> 00:06:22.860
the meth at 1.000 times the lethal dose.

122
00:06:23.110 --> 00:06:24.530
the scratches on his esophagus.

123
00:06:24.530 --> 00:06:27.140
and the plastic fragments
found in his mouth and stomach

124
00:06:27.140 --> 00:06:28.470
can all be explained.

125
00:06:28.770 --> 00:06:31.470
His route was probably provided
by the buyer as well.

126
00:06:31.470 --> 00:06:32.450
In other words.

127
00:06:32.680 --> 00:06:35.150
this Koryoin. Mr. Kim.
was a drug smuggler.

128
00:06:35.420 --> 00:06:38.940
He swallowed plastic bags containing meth
and entered the country.

129
00:06:38.940 --> 00:06:40.380
After arriving in Danhyeon.

130
00:06:40.380 --> 00:06:43.040
he damaged his esophagus
while trying to vomit the meth.

131
00:06:43.040 --> 00:06:45.570
And he died because he missed one bag—

132
00:06:45.720 --> 00:06:46.770
it was a mistake.

133
00:06:47.040 --> 00:06:48.840
According to your speculation.

134
00:06:48.850 --> 00:06:50.830
it's not homicide.

135
00:06:50.970 --> 00:06:53.270
But it seems someone dumped the body.

136
00:06:53.530 --> 00:06:55.390
If he died alone from an overdose.

137
00:06:55.440 --> 00:06:57.500
he should have had his phone with him.

138
00:07:03.120 --> 00:07:05.580
[List of Seized Items: Blood (Meth). Blood (Nicotine). Gloves. Foreign Object
(Plastic fragment A). Foreign Object (Plastic fragment B). Passport. Cigarette Butt. Lighter]

139
00:07:03.200 --> 00:07:05.590
But no phone was found at the scene.

140
00:07:05.810 --> 00:07:07.450
Whether there was a murder or not
is hard to say.

141
00:07:07.450 --> 00:07:09.710
but someone definitely dumped the body.

142
00:07:09.940 --> 00:07:13.090
And this person took Mr. Kim's phone.

143
00:07:13.330 --> 00:07:16.410
Yes. Also. a glove
was dropped near the body.

144
00:07:21.030 --> 00:07:22.490
[Glove. 1 piece]

145
00:07:22.050 --> 00:07:23.450
But no DNA was found on it.

146
00:07:23.540 --> 00:07:24.330
Also.

147
00:07:25.060 --> 00:07:26.990
why would someone who dumped a body

148
00:07:27.090 --> 00:07:28.770
throw away their glove
and leave so mindlessly?

149
00:07:28.770 --> 00:07:30.050
There was only one glove.

150
00:07:30.050 --> 00:07:32.180
They didn't throw it away on purpose.
They might've dropped it by accident.

151
00:07:32.180 --> 00:07:33.590
It was raining heavily that day.

152
00:07:33.590 --> 00:07:35.990
He must not have known
since it was chaotic.

153
00:07:36.300 --> 00:07:39.030
You act as if you've made
some amazing discovery.

154
00:07:39.230 --> 00:07:40.760
teaching me how to do my job.

155
00:07:42.090 --> 00:07:43.150
I'm sorry.

156
00:07:44.210 --> 00:07:45.370
I'm not done yet.

157
00:07:46.980 --> 00:07:47.840
Huh?

158
00:07:58.430 --> 00:08:00.350
What about the needle mark on his neck

159
00:08:00.350 --> 00:08:02.380
and the nicotine levels?

160
00:08:03.430 --> 00:08:05.490
The nicotine levels weren't lethal.

161
00:08:06.070 --> 00:08:09.900
Generally. drug addicts might accidentally
get pricked by needles when unconscious.

162
00:08:09.900 --> 00:08:12.500
Those addicted to drugs
usually smoke as well.

163
00:08:12.600 --> 00:08:15.280
Do you think these details
are unrelated to the death.

164
00:08:15.280 --> 00:08:17.920
and you can just brush them off?

165
00:08:19.590 --> 00:08:21.760
Where did you learn this kind of attitude?

166
00:08:21.760 --> 00:08:23.000
I'm sorry.

167
00:08:25.150 --> 00:08:27.430
I'll take the liberty
of not using honorifics with you.

168
00:08:27.430 --> 00:08:28.560
Please bear with me.

169
00:08:29.330 --> 00:08:31.840
Just thinking of how
you are the son of a murderer

170
00:08:31.840 --> 00:08:35.950
makes me lose any interest
in being polite.

171
00:08:36.820 --> 00:08:39.010
Ma'am. you can't just come in here.

172
00:08:39.240 --> 00:08:40.480
Prosecutor!

173
00:08:40.659 --> 00:08:42.390
My child is really
not that kind of person.

174
00:08:42.390 --> 00:08:43.640
Prosecutor!

175
00:08:44.920 --> 00:08:45.850
What's going on?

176
00:08:47.000 --> 00:08:48.480
How is this a murder?

177
00:08:48.620 --> 00:08:51.150
He didn't know the person
would actually die.

178
00:08:51.350 --> 00:08:53.300
This kid has always had a bad temper.

179
00:08:53.300 --> 00:08:55.560
He just wanted to scare them.

180
00:08:55.860 --> 00:08:57.260
Injury leading to death.

181
00:08:57.840 --> 00:08:59.370
That's your stance. right?

182
00:09:00.290 --> 00:09:02.490
And that the injury was accidental too.

183
00:09:02.650 --> 00:09:05.720
No. my son is so kind;
he would never do that.

184
00:09:06.090 --> 00:09:08.350
Do you know how obedient and kind
he was as a child?

185
00:09:08.350 --> 00:09:10.940
He's a kid
who wouldn't even dare kill a little ant.

186
00:09:10.940 --> 00:09:12.740
Someone must have made him do it.

187
00:09:13.110 --> 00:09:15.930
My child is truly innocent. Prosecutor.

188
00:09:16.290 --> 00:09:17.410
I'm innocent.

189
00:09:17.940 --> 00:09:19.110
I never did that.

190
00:09:19.310 --> 00:09:20.950
My child isn't that kind of person.

191
00:09:20.950 --> 00:09:22.470
It was a mistake.

192
00:09:24.200 --> 00:09:25.850
Don't you find it disgusting?

193
00:09:25.850 --> 00:09:28.310
That they always say
they did nothing wrong.

194
00:09:29.260 --> 00:09:30.420
Section Chief Song.

195
00:09:31.180 --> 00:09:31.940
Yes.

196
00:09:32.310 --> 00:09:34.110
What are you standing there for?

197
00:09:41.080 --> 00:09:43.480
My child has been terribly wronged.

198
00:09:44.190 --> 00:09:48.010
He's going to rot in prison
for the rest of his life.

199
00:09:48.720 --> 00:09:52.610
Just kill him! Kill him!

200
00:09:54.900 --> 00:09:56.990
Ma'am. you can't be like this.

201
00:09:57.790 --> 00:09:59.050
Get up.

202
00:10:01.400 --> 00:10:02.890
Prosecutor!

203
00:10:04.270 --> 00:10:06.150
Prosecutor!

204
00:10:06.760 --> 00:10:10.640
This is the only legal way
to kill a murderer—

205
00:10:11.760 --> 00:10:13.220
by becoming a prosecutor.

206
00:10:18.140 --> 00:10:18.980
What's wrong?

207
00:10:19.940 --> 00:10:21.340
Do you feel sorry for her?

208
00:10:21.590 --> 00:10:22.450
What?

209
00:10:23.010 --> 00:10:24.940
You must have thought that. right?

210
00:10:26.030 --> 00:10:28.180
"My dad isn't that kind of person."

211
00:10:28.700 --> 00:10:30.200
I never thought that.

212
00:10:30.370 --> 00:10:31.950
No. you did.

213
00:10:34.130 --> 00:10:38.590
Do you know what's most important
when handling a case?

214
00:10:39.670 --> 00:10:41.320
Isn't it to do it right?

215
00:10:41.590 --> 00:10:43.020
No. you're wrong.

216
00:10:45.060 --> 00:10:47.160
It's being ruthless.

217
00:10:48.990 --> 00:10:51.530
Towards those murdering bastards.

218
00:10:52.250 --> 00:10:55.380
we have to demand the maximum sentence
within our power.

219
00:10:56.920 --> 00:11:00.460
Even if the judge
gives an absurd sentence during the trial

220
00:11:00.590 --> 00:11:02.790
and my logic is completely overturned.

221
00:11:03.130 --> 00:11:04.850
before the trial prosecutor

222
00:11:05.490 --> 00:11:09.320
officially goes to court
with the case files.

223
00:11:12.230 --> 00:11:14.350
that bastard is on my scale.

224
00:11:16.200 --> 00:11:20.450
I will place the heaviest weight
I can on the other side of the scale.

225
00:11:20.710 --> 00:11:25.010
Only then can this world
be a little more balanced.

226
00:11:25.430 --> 00:11:26.410
Don't you agree?

227
00:11:28.040 --> 00:11:29.170
Yes.

228
00:11:35.910 --> 00:11:37.040
Section Chief Song.

229
00:11:37.040 --> 00:11:37.950
Yes.

230
00:11:38.410 --> 00:11:41.020
Please make sure people like that

231
00:11:41.480 --> 00:11:44.240
don't come into my office
without my permission.

232
00:11:44.830 --> 00:11:46.600
Okay. understood.

233
00:11:47.160 --> 00:11:49.060
Let's all get off work for today.

234
00:11:50.720 --> 00:11:51.780
Um. Prosecutor Ju.

235
00:11:53.930 --> 00:11:56.190
Aren't we having a dinner
to welcome Mr. Lee?

236
00:11:56.190 --> 00:11:58.720
Besides. it's Friday—
the timing is perfect.

237
00:12:06.660 --> 00:12:08.920
Mr. Lee.
even if it's just the two of us...

238
00:12:14.180 --> 00:12:15.070
Let's go.

239
00:12:20.370 --> 00:12:21.300
Awesome!

240
00:12:21.500 --> 00:12:22.120
Yes!

241
00:12:22.390 --> 00:12:23.380
Let's go!

242
00:12:29.760 --> 00:12:30.620
Cheers!

243
00:12:38.110 --> 00:12:39.130
Meat.

244
00:12:39.390 --> 00:12:40.200
Meat.

245
00:12:40.410 --> 00:12:41.200
Meat.

246
00:12:43.970 --> 00:12:45.100
Why?

247
00:12:45.400 --> 00:12:46.630
That was an onion.

248
00:12:46.810 --> 00:12:49.030
Huh! This little onion—

249
00:12:49.360 --> 00:12:52.170
how dare it cover itself in sauce.
pretending to be meat.

250
00:12:52.170 --> 00:12:53.860
I'll look for the meat for you.

251
00:12:57.840 --> 00:12:58.830
How is it?

252
00:12:59.400 --> 00:13:00.600
Do you feel betrayed?

253
00:13:01.090 --> 00:13:01.950
What?

254
00:13:02.570 --> 00:13:04.850
You ate it thinking it was meat.

255
00:13:05.230 --> 00:13:06.960
but it turned out to be an onion.

256
00:13:09.260 --> 00:13:10.510
This onion

257
00:13:10.950 --> 00:13:11.970
tried its best.

258
00:13:12.690 --> 00:13:13.950
Even covered in sauce.

259
00:13:14.430 --> 00:13:16.890
you can tell it's an onion
with just one bite.

260
00:13:18.080 --> 00:13:20.340
No matter how much it pretends to be meat.

261
00:13:20.820 --> 00:13:23.020
it will only make people feel betrayed.

262
00:13:25.080 --> 00:13:27.550
We all have a side we want to hide.
don't we?

263
00:13:29.340 --> 00:13:30.740
Oh. found it!

264
00:13:30.950 --> 00:13:31.680
The meat!

265
00:13:31.900 --> 00:13:32.710
Say "ah"!

266
00:13:33.720 --> 00:13:35.150
You can have it.

267
00:13:35.270 --> 00:13:36.070
Sure.

268
00:13:40.290 --> 00:13:41.770
Your glasses are empty.

269
00:13:42.380 --> 00:13:43.300
Senior.

270
00:13:46.900 --> 00:13:48.000
Mr. Lee.

271
00:13:50.840 --> 00:13:51.830
Me.

272
00:13:52.360 --> 00:13:53.240
Thank you.

273
00:13:54.070 --> 00:13:55.860
Come on. let's once again

274
00:13:56.300 --> 00:13:59.510
toast to welcome Supervisor Lee.

275
00:14:09.580 --> 00:14:10.720
Mr. Lee...

276
00:14:12.280 --> 00:14:13.180
I...

277
00:14:15.270 --> 00:14:17.520
am so happy to have this chance

278
00:14:18.360 --> 00:14:20.940
to get to know you.

279
00:14:58.210 --> 00:14:59.970
Do you not like me?

280
00:15:01.400 --> 00:15:03.260
Seems like you want me to like you.

281
00:15:04.350 --> 00:15:07.410
I hope you can just treat me
as Investigator Lee Chaeha.

282
00:15:07.550 --> 00:15:08.550
Is this an order?

283
00:15:08.980 --> 00:15:09.890
No.

284
00:15:10.810 --> 00:15:12.430
It's a request.

285
00:15:12.990 --> 00:15:14.470
The right to judge is mine.

286
00:15:14.880 --> 00:15:17.400
To judge how different
Investigator Lee Chaeha is

287
00:15:17.400 --> 00:15:19.670
from Lee Chaeha. the son of a murderer.

288
00:15:21.310 --> 00:15:23.640
and how qualified he is as a human.

289
00:15:24.320 --> 00:15:25.810
I will do my best.

290
00:15:27.500 --> 00:15:28.640
You've got guts.

291
00:15:29.380 --> 00:15:30.980
I thought you would run away.

292
00:15:38.230 --> 00:15:40.080
Please excuse me for a moment.

293
00:15:51.310 --> 00:15:52.060
Oh?

294
00:15:52.480 --> 00:15:53.630
Why did you come out?

295
00:15:53.900 --> 00:15:54.910
Where did you go?

296
00:15:55.380 --> 00:15:57.140
I went to buy ice cream.

297
00:15:57.520 --> 00:15:58.690
In the middle of winter?

298
00:15:58.690 --> 00:16:00.420
I felt like I needed to sober up.

299
00:16:00.480 --> 00:16:01.660
You go home first.

300
00:16:01.820 --> 00:16:02.950
I'll join you later.

301
00:16:03.140 --> 00:16:04.030
What?

302
00:16:04.460 --> 00:16:06.370
I'll take Section Chief Song home first.

303
00:16:06.370 --> 00:16:07.650
Then I'm going back to the office

304
00:16:07.650 --> 00:16:08.850
to pick something up.

305
00:16:13.870 --> 00:16:15.000
Prosecutor Ju!

306
00:16:15.750 --> 00:16:16.690
Supervisor Lee!

307
00:16:17.210 --> 00:16:18.980
Come on. let's go for round two.

308
00:16:19.380 --> 00:16:21.700
-Song Haneul's treat.
-Let's go. Mr. Song.

309
00:16:21.700 --> 00:16:22.870
Let's go for round two.

310
00:16:22.870 --> 00:16:23.700
Get in the car.

311
00:16:23.970 --> 00:16:25.430
We have to go for round two.

312
00:16:26.280 --> 00:16:27.600
-Let's go.
-All right. step back.

313
00:16:27.600 --> 00:16:28.440
Let me do it.

314
00:16:29.750 --> 00:16:32.730
Hey. Mr. Lee. get in.

315
00:16:35.870 --> 00:16:37.150
-Let's go together!
-Get in.

316
00:16:37.150 --> 00:16:39.070
Mr. Lee. get in quickly.

317
00:17:17.089 --> 00:17:19.599
You opened the door
without checking who it was.

318
00:17:19.599 --> 00:17:21.810
Haven't you seen people
get killed doing things like that?

319
00:17:21.810 --> 00:17:22.920
I have.

320
00:17:25.619 --> 00:17:27.480
What are you waiting for? Move it.

321
00:17:38.180 --> 00:17:39.240
[Neulocan Extended-Release Tablet.
Sedative-hypnotic drug]

322
00:18:03.390 --> 00:18:07.110
I've compiled several types of cases
in Danhyeon over the past 10 years.

323
00:18:07.110 --> 00:18:08.640
Analyze them within a week.

324
00:18:08.910 --> 00:18:11.790
See you in the office
at 7:00 a.m. on Wednesday.

325
00:18:12.380 --> 00:18:13.490
A week?

326
00:18:27.070 --> 00:18:27.930
What?

327
00:18:28.570 --> 00:18:29.530
Can't do it?

328
00:18:43.130 --> 00:18:44.340
I can.

329
00:19:15.760 --> 00:19:17.430
Why me?

330
00:19:18.280 --> 00:19:22.230
Are you asking why
I transferred you to my office?

331
00:19:24.390 --> 00:19:27.840
Do you remember what you said to me
the night I drove you home

332
00:19:28.250 --> 00:19:29.850
after eating Gukbap?

333
00:19:31.320 --> 00:19:33.570
Uh. I said I've always respected you.

334
00:19:46.740 --> 00:19:48.070
Are you leaving now?

335
00:20:05.390 --> 00:20:06.670
I feel sick.

336
00:20:07.310 --> 00:20:08.600
Say that again.

337
00:20:09.120 --> 00:20:11.560
Prosecutor. I respect—

338
00:20:11.670 --> 00:20:14.330
How dare the son of a murderer
say he respects me.

339
00:20:15.190 --> 00:20:17.970
Don't use force. or you'll die.

340
00:20:27.450 --> 00:20:29.210
Why do you hate me so much?

341
00:20:29.400 --> 00:20:30.730
Don't play dumb with me.

342
00:20:33.600 --> 00:20:37.330
I loathe you with every fiber of my being
because you are Lee Chaeha.

343
00:20:49.270 --> 00:20:50.530
Don't you hate me?

344
00:20:51.930 --> 00:20:56.830
Whatever I do to you.
you just have to take it.

345
00:21:07.240 --> 00:21:09.380
[The Prosecutor's Proposal]

346
00:21:09.460 --> 00:21:13.970
[Next Episode]

347
00:21:09.510 --> 00:21:11.290
Because I don't want to run away.

348
00:21:11.290 --> 00:21:12.130
I'm curious—

349
00:21:12.300 --> 00:21:13.950
who will give up first?

350
00:21:14.100 --> 00:21:15.330
[Lee Chaeha. Top Police Graduate:
"A World Where the Innocent Aren't Wronged"]

351
00:21:14.100 --> 00:21:16.670
Does he actually think
his dad is innocent?

352
00:21:16.700 --> 00:21:20.220
After pushing us seniors aside to get the investigator position
in the prosecutor's office.

353
00:21:20.220 --> 00:21:21.750
you've become so arrogant.

354
00:21:21.800 --> 00:21:22.600
One.

355
00:21:22.870 --> 00:21:23.450
Two.

356
00:21:23.620 --> 00:21:24.400
Three.

357
00:21:24.620 --> 00:21:25.460
Four.

358
00:21:25.480 --> 00:21:26.410
A whole 20 times.

359
00:21:26.550 --> 00:21:27.380
Overkill.

360
00:21:27.520 --> 00:21:29.580
Lee Gilyoung also killed someone
with an awl.

361
00:21:29.580 --> 00:21:31.890
Maybe the murder weapon wasn't an awl.

362
00:21:32.050 --> 00:21:35.440
I heard Lee Gilyoung's son even submitted
his diary from that day as evidence

363
00:21:35.440 --> 00:21:36.430
and testified in court.

364
00:21:36.430 --> 00:21:37.460
Who would believe

365
00:21:37.700 --> 00:21:39.020
the words of a murderer's son?

366
00:21:39.020 --> 00:21:42.040
Supervisor Lee. didn't we agree you would resign
and go back to the fine department?

366
00:21:43.305 --> 00:22:43.516
